        <img src="../../assets/united_states-bosnia_erzegovina-worldcup22026.jpg" class="cover-hero" alt="The USA face Bosnia-Herzegovina at the MetLife Stadium in a must-win match. Discover the lineups and tactical analysis of the eve.">
        <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #666; font-style: italic; margin-top: -8px; margin-bottom: 20px;">The electric atmosphere at the MetLife Stadium ready to host the decisive clash between the USA and Bosnia-Herzegovina.</p>

        <div class="content">
            <p>Tension is running high in New York on the eve of a match that already feels like a do-or-die clash. Under the floodlights of the majestic <strong>MetLife Stadium</strong>, on <strong>July 2, 2026, at 02:00 CEST</strong>, the <strong>United States</strong> will play for a major part of their international football future against a always tough <strong>Bosnia-Herzegovina</strong>. The Stars and Stripes, coming off a slow start to the tournament, have no alternative but to win to banish the ghosts of an early exit in front of their home crowd.</p><h3>The MetLife roar to banish the ghosts of a slow start</h3><p>Argentine coach <strong>Pochettino</strong> knows very well that the pressure is entirely on his players' shoulders. Playing at home is a great advantage, but it can turn into a source of anxiety if the goal is slow to come. The nation's eyes will be on <strong>Pulisic</strong>, the guiding star of the US attack, called upon to carry the team and break through the opposing defense with his lightning accelerations. The key to the match will be intensity in the opening minutes: pressing high to ignite the New Jersey crowd.</p><h3>Barbarez's defensive web and the eternal Dzeko factor</h3><p>On the other side, the Balkan national team led by <strong>Barbarez</strong> approaches the fixture with the serenity of those who have everything to gain and a well-defined tactical plan. Bosnia-Herzegovina will deploy a low and compact defensive line, ready to close every central passing lane and then trigger lethal counter-attacks. The offensive target and absolute reference point remains the timeless <strong>Dzeko</strong>, a striker capable of holding up the ball and leading the team during moments of maximum pressure.</p><h3>Pochettino's moves to unleash star man Pulisic</h3><p>To overcome the wall built by the Slavs, Pochettino will rely on the dynamism of a robust midfield led by <strong>Adams</strong> and the creativity of <strong>McKennie</strong> as an advanced playmaker. The goal is to create numerical superiority on the flanks to deliver inviting crosses for <strong>Balogun</strong>. It will be crucial not to concede quick transitions to Bosnia, who can punish the American defense at the slightest distraction with the physical presence of <strong>Demirovic</strong> and Dzeko's experience.</p><h3>The official predicted lineups on the pitch</h3><div class="lineups"><p><strong>United States (4-2-3-1):</strong> Freese; Freeman, Ream, Richards, Robinson; Adams, Tillman; Dest, McKennie, Pulisic; Balogun.</p><p class="coach">Ct: Pochettino</p><br><p><strong>Bosnia-Herzegovina (4-4-2):</strong> Vasilj; Dedic, Katic, Muharemovic, Kolasinac; Bajraktarevic, Sunjic, Basic, Alajbegovic; Dzeko, Demirovic.</p><p class="coach">Ct: Barbarez</p></div>
        </div>

